+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PQf8Zm1EiQXGodA5p6632V","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# T3: Full-Text Search Feature\n     2→\n     3→## Category\n     4→features/medium\n     5→\n     6→## Timeout\n     7→30 minutes\n     8→\n     9→## Description\n    10→An existing Express + SQLite note-taking API has CRUD endpoints for notes (title, body, tags, timestamps) and tag-based filtering. Add full-text search using SQLite FTS5.\n    11→\n    12→## Requirements\n    13→\n    14→### 1. Search Endpoint: `GET /notes/search?q=<query>`\n    15→- Full-text search across note titles and bodies using SQLite FTS5\n    16→- Results ranked by relevance (BM25 ranking)\n    17→- Snippet highlighting with `<mark>` tags around matched terms\n    18→- Quoted phrase support (e.g., `?q=\"exact phrase\"`)\n    19→- Pagination: 20 results per page, controlled by `?page=N` parameter\n    20→- Response format: `{ results: SearchResult[], total: number, page: number, perPage: number }`\n    21→- Returns 400 if `q` parameter is missing or empty\n    22→\n    23→### 2. Suggest Endpoint: `GET /notes/search/suggest?q=<prefix>`\n    24→- Autocomplete that returns up to 5 matching note titles\n    25→- Matches prefix against note content (title and body)\n    26→- Response format: `{ results: SuggestResult[] }`\n    27→- Returns 400 if `q` parameter is missing or empty\n    28→\n    29→### 3. FTS Index Synchronization\n    30→- FTS index must stay in sync when notes are created, updated, or deleted\n    31→- Use SQLite triggers or manual sync in the CRUD operations\n    32→\n    33→## Interfaces (already defined in `src/models.ts`)\n    34→\n    35→```ts\n    36→interface SearchResult {\n    37→  id: number;\n    38→  title: string;\n    39→  snippet: string;  // with <mark> highlighting\n    40→  rank: number;\n    41→}\n    42→\n    43→interface SuggestResult {\n    44→  id: number;\n    45→  title: string;\n    46→}\n    47→```\n    48→\n    49→## Existing Code\n    50→- `src/db.ts` - Database setup with `notes` table\n    51→- `src/models.ts` - TypeScript interfaces (SearchResult and SuggestResult already defined)\n    52→- `src/routes.ts` - CRUD routes for notes\n    53→- `src/errors.ts` - Error handling middleware\n    54→- `src/server.ts` - Express app setup\n    55→- `src/seed.ts` - Seed script with ~50 sample notes\n    56→\n    57→## Tests\n    58→- `tests/notes.test.ts` - 15 existing CRUD tests (must continue passing)\n    59→- `tests/search.test.ts` - 20 search tests (must pass after implementation)\n    60→\n    61→## Validation\n    62→```bash\n    63→npm test\n    64→```\n    65→All 35 tests must pass.\n    66→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01U5LMNKPkKpELVakwckwUr3","session_id":"dd759fa8-2b0a-48dd-b8de-444b3369a0bd","uuid":"52412beb-9beb-4aab-a872-9c9178730ad1"}
