+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01U5LMNKPkKpELVakwckwUr3","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary of all the files and their contents:\n\n## Complete Codebase Overview\n\n### Project Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── package.json                 (Dependencies & scripts)\n├── package-lock.json            (Dependency lock file)\n├── tsconfig.json                (TypeScript config)\n├── vitest.config.ts             (Test config)\n├── .eslintrc.cjs                (ESLint config)\n├── TASK.md                       (Task requirements)\n├── src/\n│   ├── db.ts                     (Database setup & seeding)\n│   ├── models.ts                 (TypeScript interfaces)\n│   ├── routes.ts                 (CRUD routes)\n│   ├── errors.ts                 (Error handling)\n│   ├── server.ts                 (Express app setup)\n│   └── seed.ts                   (Seed script)\n└── tests/\n    ├── notes.test.ts             (15 CRUD tests)\n    └── search.test.ts            (20 search tests)\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Contents\n\n### /workspace/package.json\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-fts-search\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Full-text search feature benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\",\n    \"seed\": \"tsx src/seed.ts\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"better-sqlite3\": \"^11.0.0\",\n    \"express\": \"^4.21.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/better-sqlite3\": \"^7.6.0\",\n    \"@types/express\": \"^4.17.0\",\n    \"supertest\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/supertest\": \"^6.0.0\",\n    \"tsx\": \"^4.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### /workspace/src/db.ts\n```typescript\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\n\nexport function createDatabase(path?: string): Database.Database {\n  const db = path ? new Database(path) : new Database(':memory:');\n\n  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n  db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');\n\n  // Create notes table\n  db.exec(`\n    CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS notes (\n      id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n      title TEXT NOT NULL,\n      body TEXT NOT NULL,\n      tags TEXT DEFAULT '[]',\n      created_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\n      updated_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now'))\n    )\n  `);\n\n  return db;\n}\n\nexport function seedDatabase(db: Database.Database): void {\n  const insert = db.prepare(`\n    INSERT INTO notes (title, body, tags) VALUES (?, ?, ?)\n  `);\n\n  const notes = getSeedNotes();\n\n  const insertMany = db.transaction((items: { title: string; body: string; tags: string }[]) => {\n    for (const item of items) {\n      insert.run(item.title, item.body, item.tags);\n    }\n  });\n\n  insertMany(notes);\n}\n\nfunction getSeedNotes(): { title: string; body: string; tags: string }[] {\n  return [\n    // 45 seed notes with various topics:\n    // - Programming (TypeScript, Python, React, Docker, Kubernetes, Rust, Machine Learning)\n    // - Travel (Tokyo, Paris, Southeast Asia, Appalachian Trail, Nordic Hiking, Kilimanjaro)\n    // - Cooking (Pasta, Cookies, Risotto, French Cooking, Thai Cooking, Espresso, Coffee Roasting)\n    // - Science (Quantum Computing, Solar System, Climate Change, Neural Networks)\n    // - Music (Guitar, Jazz, Classical)\n    // - Health (Mediterranean Diet, Yoga, Sleep, Meditation)\n    // - Photography (Composition, Astrophotography)\n    // - Art (Photography, Watercolor Painting)\n    // - Web (GraphQL vs REST, Accessibility, CSS Grid)\n    // - Outdoor (Hiking, Photography)\n    // - And more...\n  ];\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### /workspace/src/models.ts\n```typescript\nexport interface Note {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags: string; // JSON array as string\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n\nexport interface NoteInput {\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n}\n\nexport interface SearchResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  snippet: string;\n  rank: number;\n}\n\nexport interface SuggestResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### /workspace/src/routes.ts\n```typescript\nimport { Router, Request, Response, NextFunction } from 'express';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { Note, NoteInput } from './models.js';\nimport { NotFoundError, ValidationError } from './errors.js';\n\nexport function createRoutes(db: Database.Database): Router {\n  const router = Router();\n\n  // GET /notes - List all notes (with optional tag filter)\n  router.get('/notes', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n    try {\n      const tag = req.query.tag as string | undefined;\n\n      let notes: Note[];\n      if (tag) {\n        // Use a join with json_each for tag filtering\n        const tagStmt = db.prepare(`\n          SELECT DISTINCT notes.* FROM notes, json_each(notes.tags)\n          WHERE json_each.value = ?\n          ORDER BY created_at DESC\n        `);\n        notes = tagStmt.all(tag) as Note[];\n      } else {\n        const stmt = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM notes ORDER BY created_at DESC');\n        notes = stmt.all() as Note[];\n      }\n\n      res.json({ notes });\n    } catch (err) {\n      next(err);\n    }\n  });\n\n  // GET /notes/:id - Get single note\n  router.get('/notes/:id', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n    try {\n      const id = parseInt(req.params.id);\n      const stmt = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM notes WHERE id = ?');\n      const note = stmt.get(id) as Note | undefined;\n\n      if (!note) {\n        throw new NotFoundError('Note not found');\n      }\n\n      res.json({ note });\n    } catch (err) {\n      next(err);\n    }\n  });\n\n  // POST /notes - Create note\n  router.post('/notes', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n    try {\n      const input = req.body as NoteInput;\n\n      if (!input.title || input.title.trim() === '') {\n        throw new ValidationError('Title is required');\n      }\n      if (!input.body || input.body.trim() === '') {\n        throw new ValidationError('Body is required');\n      }\n\n      const tags = input.tags ? JSON.stringify(input.tags) : '[]';\n      const stmt = db.prepare(`\n        INSERT INTO notes (title, body, tags) VALUES (?, ?, ?)\n      `);\n      const result = stmt.run(input.title, input.body, tags);\n\n      const note = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM notes WHERE id = ?').get(result.lastInsertRowid) as Note;\n      res.status(201).json({ note });\n    } catch (err) {\n      next(err);\n    }\n  });\n\n  // PUT /notes/:id - Update note\n  router.put('/notes/:id', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n    try {\n      const id = parseInt(req.params.id);\n      const existing = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM notes WHERE id = ?').get(id) as Note | undefined;\n\n      if (!existing) {\n        throw new NotFoundError('Note not found');\n      }\n\n      const input = req.body as Partial<NoteInput>;\n      const title = input.title ?? existing.title;\n      const body = input.body ?? existing.body;\n      const tags = input.tags ? JSON.stringify(input.tags) : existing.tags;\n\n      const stmt = db.prepare(`\n        UPDATE notes SET title = ?, body = ?, tags = ?, updated_at = datetime('now')\n        WHERE id = ?\n      `);\n      stmt.run(title, body, tags, id);\n\n      const note = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM notes WHERE id = ?').get(id) as Note;\n      res.json({ note });\n    } catch (err) {\n      next(err);\n    }\n  });\n\n  // DELETE /notes/:id - Delete note\n  router.delete('/notes/:id', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n    try {\n      const id = parseInt(req.params.id);\n      const existing = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM notes WHERE id = ?').get(id) as Note | undefined;\n\n      if (!existing) {\n        throw new NotFoundError('Note not found');\n      }\n\n      db.prepare('DELETE FROM notes WHERE id = ?').run(id);\n      res.status(204).send();\n    } catch (err) {\n      next(err);\n    }\n  });\n\n  return router;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### /workspace/src/errors.ts\n```typescript\nimport { Request, Response, NextFunction } from 'express';\n\nexport class NotFoundError extends Error {\n  statusCode = 404;\n  constructor(message = 'Resource not found') {\n    super(message);\n    this.name = 'NotFoundError';\n  }\n}\n\nexport class ValidationError extends Error {\n  statusCode = 400;\n  constructor(message = 'Validation failed') {\n    super(message);\n    this.name = 'ValidationError';\n  }\n}\n\nexport function errorHandler(\n  err: Error,\n  _req: Request,\n  res: Response,\n  _next: NextFunction\n): void {\n  if (err instanceof NotFoundError) {\n    res.status(err.statusCode).json({ error: err.message });\n  } else if (err instanceof ValidationError) {\n    res.status(err.statusCode).json({ error: err.message });\n  } else {\n    console.error(err);\n    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Internal server error' });\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### /workspace/src/server.ts\n```typescript\nimport express from 'express';\nimport { createDatabase, seedDatabase } from './db.js';\nimport { createRoutes } from './routes.js';\nimport { errorHandler } from './errors.js';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\n\nexport interface App {\n  app: express.Express;\n  db: Database.Database;\n}\n\nexport function createApp(dbPath?: string): App {\n  const db = createDatabase(dbPath);\n  const app = express();\n\n  app.use(express.json());\n\n  const routes = createRoutes(db);\n  app.use(routes);\n\n  app.use(errorHandler);\n\n  return { app, db };\n}\n\nexport function createSeededApp(dbPath?: string): App {\n  const { app, db } = createApp(dbPath);\n  seedDatabase(db);\n  return { app, db };\n}\n\n// Start server if run directly\nconst isMain = process.argv[1]?.endsWith('server.js') || process.argv[1]?.endsWith('server.ts');\nif (isMain) {\n  const { app } = createSeededApp();\n  const port = process.env.PORT || 3000;\n  app.listen(port, () => {\n    console.log(`Server running on port ${port}`);\n  });\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### /workspace/src/seed.ts\n```typescript\nimport { createDatabase, seedDatabase } from './db.js';\n\nconst dbPath = process.argv[2] || 'notes.db';\nconsole.log(`Seeding database at: ${dbPath}`);\n\nconst db = createDatabase(dbPath);\nseedDatabase(db);\n\nconst count = (db.prepare('SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM notes').get() as { count: number }).count;\nconsole.log(`Seeded ${count} notes successfully.`);\n\ndb.close();\n```\n\n---\n\n### /workspace/tests/search.test.ts\nComprehensive test suite with 20 tests covering:\n\n1. **Basic Search** (Tests 1-3):\n   - Returns matching notes for a keyword query\n   - Results include snippet field\n   - Snippets contain `<mark>` tags around matched terms\n\n2. **Relevance Ranking** (Test 4):\n   - Results ranked by relevance (BM25)\n   - Rank values in ascending order\n\n3. **Phrase Queries** (Test 5):\n   - Exact phrase matching with quotes (e.g., \"chocolate chip\")\n\n4. **Response Format** (Test 6):\n   - Returns id, title, snippet, rank fields\n\n5. **Empty Results** (Test 7):\n   - Non-existent terms return empty array\n\n6. **Query Validation** (Tests 8-9):\n   - Missing `q` parameter returns 400\n   - Empty `q` parameter returns 400\n\n7. **Pagination** (Tests 10-12):\n   - Page 1 returns up to 20 results\n   - Page 2 returns next batch\n   - Response includes total count\n\n8. **Suggest Endpoint** (Tests 13-15):\n   - `/notes/search/suggest?q=prefix` returns up to 5 titles\n   - Results match prefix in title\n   - Empty suggest query returns 400\n\n9. **FTS Synchronization** (Tests 16-18):\n   - FTS syncs 